<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-07T10:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-09-07T10:41:00-05:00" n="253" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d253">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/824</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LM1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Langhorne</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-07T17:00:00+01:19">
                                        <hi rend="italic">September 7, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 9.40 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1319. Legation informed that it is the opinion in German circles in
                                Holland that general effect of President’s reply to Pope’s message
                                will be to temporarily retard democratic reform in Germany and that
                                the note has furnished new fighting material to the Conservatives
                                and the military party.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LM1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Langhorne</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>